'''''Star Wars'' 16''' is the sixteenth issue of the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']]. It was written by [[Archie Goodwin]], illustrated by series guest artists [[Walter Simonson|Walt Simonson]] and [[Bob Wiacek]], and first published by [[Marvel Comics]] on [[July 25]], [[1978]]. It features the story "'''The Hunter!'''," which introduces [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Beilert Valance/Legends|Beilert Valance]] as he tracks down [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]].

==Publisher's summary==
''When a nefarious bounter hunter [sic] mistakes another teenager for Skywalker, a battle ensues!''

==Plot summary==
[[Beilert Valance/Legends|Beilert Valance]], bounty hunter and [[Droid/Legends|droid]] hater, leads his [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] gang on a merciless attack of [[Anglebay Station]] on [[Telos IV]]. There, they find [[Don-Wan Kihotay]], who recounts his adventure with the [[Star-Hoppers of Aduba-3]]. The gang mistakes the Star-Hoppers for the group of [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] who destroyed the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]], thinking the young [[Farm/Legends|farm]] boy [[Jimm Doshun]] is actually Luke Skywalker. Thinking of the huge reward for capturing the boy who destroyed the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire's]] greatest [[Superweapon/Legends|weapon]], as well as the personal enjoyment of punishing someone who favors droids, Valance immediately sets off to find the boy. [[Jaxxon/Legends|Jaxxon]] and [[Amaiza Foxtrain/Legends|Amaiza Foxtrain]] find out about his plan and go to [[Aduba-3/Legends|Aduba-3]] to warn Jimm that the bounty hunters are after him. A battle ensues when the gang arrives, and most of them are [[Death/Legends|killed]] during the fight with the three Star-Hoppers. It is only then that Valance, the lone survivor of his gang, realizes that he was after the wrong boy the whole time, but he escapes by using the [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] built into his [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic]] arm, taking the others by surprise and leaving the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] in his [[Starship/Legends|ship]] ''[[Kill Switch]]''.

==Continuity==
''Star Wars'' 16 marked the first appearance of bounty hunter Beilert Valance, a recurring character in both the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] and [[canon]] continuities.<ref name="SW.com">{{SW|url=news/who-is-beilert-valance|text=Who is Beilert Valance?}}</ref>

